{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "13 use ESM-IF1 65 and generate 10 candidate sequences for each structure.",
    "We performed self-consistency TM score evaluation for both these methods, generating 8 candidate sequences using author-recommended temperature values (T = 1:0 for ESM-IF1, T = 0:1 for ProteinMPNN).",
    "We use OmegaFold to fold all amino acid sequences for this comparison.",
    "We found that ProteinMPNN in C α mode (i.e., alpha-carbon mode) consistently yields much stronger scTM values (Tables S2, S3); we thus adopt ProteinMPNN for our primary results.",
    "While generating more candidate sequences leads to a higher scTM score (as there are more chances to encounter a successfully folded sequence), we conservatively choose to run 8 samples to be directly comparable to ref. 15."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "13 use ESM-IF1 65 and generate 10 candidate sequences for each structure."
  ]
}